# YouTube Data API v3 key — used by the Learning Center to fetch real,
# live farming videos with real thumbnails.
#
# How to get one:
# 1. https://console.cloud.google.com/ -> create a project
# 2. APIs & Services -> Library -> search "YouTube Data API v3" -> Enable
# 3. APIs & Services -> Credentials -> + Create Credentials -> API key
# 4. Restrict the key: API restrictions -> YouTube Data API v3 only
#    Application restrictions -> Websites -> your domain(s)
#
# Without this key, the Learning Center falls back to a small set of
# verified static videos instead of live search.
VITE_YOUTUBE_API_KEY=AIzaSyAVip_tgTbzSFqjV5HnLB83lm0v4SCrKr0

# data.gov.in API key — used by the Market Price Dashboard for live
# mandi (market) prices via the Agmarknet dataset.
#
# How to get one:
# 1. https://data.gov.in/ -> Sign Up / Login
# 2. https://data.gov.in/user/me/apis -> generate your API key
# 3. Paste it below
#
# Without this key, the Market Price Dashboard falls back to static
# sample data instead of live prices.
VITE_DATA_GOV_IN_API_KEY=579b464db66ec23bdd000001cdd3946e44ce4aad7209ff7b23ac571b

# Gemini API key — used by two AI features:
#  1. AI Disease Detection — sends uploaded crop photos to Gemini
#     (vision) for a real, reasoned visual read. This is NOT a
#     certified plant-pathology model — it's general AI vision with
#     a carefully constrained prompt, framed as a helpful first look
#     rather than a diagnosis.
#  2. AI Assistant (floating chat widget) — multi-turn farming Q&A
#     covering crops, irrigation, soil, weather decisions, government
#     schemes, market timing, and pest/disease basics.
# Both features always tell users to confirm high-stakes guidance
# (pesticide dosing, treatments, etc.) with a local agricultural
# extension officer or the app's Expert Consultation feature.
#
# This uses gemini-2.5-flash-lite, which is FREE on Google's free tier
# (no credit card required, generous daily request limits).
#
# How to get one:
# 1. https://aistudio.google.com/apikey -> Get API Key -> Create API Key
#    (no billing setup needed for the free tier)
#
# IMPORTANT: this key must be set server-side only (as GEMINI_API_KEY
# in Netlify's environment variables, NOT with a VITE_ prefix) — it is
# read by netlify/functions/disease-detection.js and
# netlify/functions/ai-assistant.js, never exposed to the browser.
#
# Without this key, Disease Detection and the AI Assistant chat both
# show a clear notice instead of attempting a request.
GEMINI_API_KEY=AQ.Ab8RN6IJCGCdbyhR5fdHu-dXta0NPztwXsUVe1hpoKZVfA50xA
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# EmailJS — used by the Village Civic Services module to email a
# submitted complaint to a demo authority inbox and send the
# citizen a confirmation copy. Both emails reuse the SAME
# EmailJS service + template ID below (just a different
# recipient) — no need to create two separate templates. This is
# a demo/community-service feature; no real authority workflow
# is wired up.
#
# How to get these:
# 1. https://www.emailjs.com/ -> sign up -> Email Services -> add
#    your email service, copy its Service ID
# 2. Email Templates -> create ONE template with a `{{to_email}}`,
#    `{{to_name}}`, `{{complaint_id}}`, `{{category}}`, and
#    `{{summary}}` variable (optionally branch wording on
#    `{{recipient_role}}`, which is "authority" or "citizen") —
#    copy its Template ID
# 3. Account -> General -> copy your Public Key
#
# Without these, the complaint is still saved locally and gets a
# real Complaint ID — only the email step is skipped (the UI
# clearly shows "Demo Mode" in that case).
VITE_EMAILJS_SERVICE_ID=service_6rgk2oi
VITE_EMAILJS_TEMPLATE_ID=template_5j4rfak
VITE_EMAILJS_PUBLIC_KEY=SyyD1sj52yI5prXoR

# Inbox that demo complaints are addressed to (any address you
# control for testing — this is not a real municipal authority).
VITE_CIVIC_AUTHORITY_EMAIL=shaiksubhani5392@gmail.com
